result.execSummary:
Michael Tyrone Wilson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Michael Tyrone Wilson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Michael Tyrone Wilson not in court.  Carole R Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant has been turned over to the State of Indiana.
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Michael Tyrone Wilson in court with attorney Jeffrey A. Schwarz.  Defendant Michael Tyrone Wilson in custody.  Deann L. Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  DEFENDANT NOW HAS A REVOCATION WITH A RELEASE DATE OF 5/7/2014.  DEFENDANT WAS ADVISE TO CONTACT ATTY. ASSOCIATED WITH REVOCATION FOR TRUE DATE OF RELEASE.  Case is adjourned for another status date.  Status conference scheduled for May 12, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Michael Tyrone Wilson in court with attorney Daryl A Kastenson.  Defendant Michael Tyrone Wilson in custody.  Carole R Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Donald, Branch 02.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Indiana.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for March 6, 2014 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
